This paper is about accelerating Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) through parameter pruning, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel probabilistic pruning method, which involves designing a mechanism to increase and decrease pruning probabilities based on importance criteria for the training process, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experiments and results, which may also suggest a focus on data structures (cs.DS) for efficient implementation.
